title: Chickpea and Winter Vegetable Stew
summary: Chickpean and Winter Vegetable Stew is a dairy free and vegetarian soup. One portion of this dish contains approximately 10g of protein, 3g of fat, and a total of 273 calories. This recipe serves 8 and costs $1.75 per serving. It will be a hit at your Autumn event. If you have ground cumin, chickpeas, couscous, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. 1 person has made this recipe and would make it again. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes about 45 minutes. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 79%. This score is pretty good. Similar recipes are Winter Squash, Chickpea & Red Lentil Stew, Winter Vegetable Beef Stew, and Hearty Winter Vegetable Stew.
instructions: Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add onion and leek; saut 5 minutes. Add coriander and next 4 ingredients (through garlic); cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add 3 cups Simple Vegetable Stock and the next 8 ingredients (through chickpeas); bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 30 minutes. Stir in parsley and honey.                                                                                                 Remove 2/3 cup hot cooking liquid from squash mixture. Place cooking liquid and remaining 2/3 cup stock in a medium bowl. Stir in couscous. Cover and let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with a fork. Serve with lemon wedges.

Add coriander and next 4 ingredients (through garlic); cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add 3 cups Simple Vegetable Stock and the next 8 ingredients (through chickpeas); bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 30 minutes. Stir in parsley and honey.
Remove 2/3 cup hot cooking liquid from squash mixture.
Place cooking liquid and remaining 2/3 cup stock in a medium bowl. Stir in couscous. Cover and let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with a fork.
